display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f=\mathsf {id}_{A}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  g = \mathsf {id}_{B}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>We will often write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> for the inverse to a bijection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
